## **Metric Glossary**

The following summarizes the intent of each metric group and

how it reflects data reliability and the benefits of

agentic AI data engineering:

* \*\*Schema Divergence Score\*\*: Captures how fragmented the schema landscape is across sources.

Automated schema matching and canonicalization directly reduce this divergence.

* \*\*Schema Overlap Percentage\*\*: Indicates how consistently different systems align to a shared schema.  
* \*\*Field-Type Variation Rate\*\*: Highlights type mismatches that can break pipelines and analytics.  
* \*\*Value Inconsistency Rate\*\*: Surfaces conflicting entity attributes that demand entity resolution.  
* \*\*Numeric Normalization Error Count\*\*: Reveals formatting and parsing issues in numeric data.  
* \*\*Date Format Diversity Index\*\*: Quantifies the complexity of harmonizing temporal data.  
* \*\*Phone Number Format Variations\*\*: Shows the effort required to normalize contact fields.  
* \*\*Structural Depth Variance & Distance\*\*: Measure how similar or divergent JSON/XML models are.  
* \*\*Clause Embedding Misclassification Rate\*\*: Evaluates semantic separability of legal clause types.  
* \*\*LLM Semantic Equivalence Accuracy\*\*: Assesses how reliably an LLM can detect near-duplicate clauses.  
* \*\*Duplicate Detection Rate & Conflict Severity\*\*: Characterize entity overlap and disagreement.  
* \*\*Golden Record Completion Rate\*\*: Indicates how complete fused entities become after merging.  
* \*\*OCR Noise Metrics\*\*: Reflect text quality and readiness for downstream NLP.
